1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:01,930
How about Junya Sakamoto?

2
00:00:02,490 --> 00:00:03,900
Now is the best time to hire him.

3
00:00:04,310 --> 00:00:06,350
Our partner brand
wanted someone with a strong

4
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,270
charisma like you
to be the image model.

5
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:09,690
We would be very grateful

6
00:00:09,730 --> 00:00:12,050
if you could lend us
your support, Mr. Sakamoto.

7
00:00:12,210 --> 00:00:14,560
How long are you going
to keep playing "Salaryman A"?

8
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:16,060
Listen.

9
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,130
You're just lying to yourself.

10
00:00:18,140 --> 00:00:19,820
You keep yourself busy to avoid it.

11
00:00:20,310 --> 00:00:21,010
Come back,

12
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:22,850
Toma.

13
00:00:29,210 --> 00:00:30,710
Thanks to everyone's effort,

14
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:34,810
we’re expecting more media
than we anticipated today.

15
00:00:35,710 --> 00:00:37,420
Let’s make this event a success.

16
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:39,830
Yeah.

17
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:49,130
So nice.

18
00:00:49,820 --> 00:00:50,630
What?

19
00:00:50,930 --> 00:00:51,690
Just imagining

20
00:00:51,740 --> 00:00:54,140
Junya walking up there
gets me fired up.

21
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,900
Just by imagining it?

22
00:00:56,540 --> 00:00:57,240
I know.

23
00:00:57,890 --> 00:00:59,410
I know exactly how you feel.

24
00:01:00,430 --> 00:01:01,780
The real thing is coming soon.

25
00:01:02,510 --> 00:01:03,380
I need to re-touch.

26
00:01:14,990 --> 00:01:16,450
You are Toma Kiryu.

27
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:17,600
Come back,

28
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:19,450
Toma.

29
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,800
I wonder if this position
is good for the camera.

30
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:30,040
I think it's good.

31
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:31,270
It's perfect.

32
00:01:32,450 --> 00:01:33,590
It almost makes me wonder

33
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:35,430
if you’ve done
this kind of work before.

34
00:01:35,830 --> 00:01:36,810
You’re exaggerating.

35
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,020
But,

36
00:01:38,380 --> 00:01:39,290
thanks for coming by.

37
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:40,440
I'm glad.

38
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:42,190
Not at all.

39
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,610
If I'm allowed to,
I'd come anytime.

40
00:01:44,570 --> 00:01:47,330
I can do anything,
I can be an alarm and wake you up.

41
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:48,780
I can make lunch for you.

42
00:01:48,980 --> 00:01:49,920
Just say it, and I'll do it.

43
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,260
Lunch, huh?

44
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,920
Maybe I'll ask one someday.

45
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:02,610


46
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:03,750
Excuse me.

47
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,470
We want to check
the lighting and positioning.

48
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,900
Could one of you
please stand on stage?

49
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:27,700
He's so handsome.

50
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,810
No, I'm not.

51
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,540
I'm his fan now.

52
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:36,040
He is the best of all the best.

53
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:47,350
I think Mr. Oishi
will be arriving very soon.

54
00:02:50,010 --> 00:02:51,830
Inspire’s director,
Mr. Oishi, has arrived.

55
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:53,910
Good morning.

56
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:56,420
Thank you for coming by.

57
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:58,140
Pleasure to meet you.
━Likewise.

58
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,480
Pleasure to meet you.
━Likewise.

59
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,140
Please come this way.

60
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:08,740
Where's Junya?

61
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:09,900
Isn't he here yet?

62
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,950
He's already 30 minutes late.

63
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:14,540
I tried calling his agency,
but no luck.

64
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:16,910
I got in touch with his manager.

65
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:18,140
What did they say?

66
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:19,320
Mr. Sakamoto,

67
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:21,200
was already on his way here but

68
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:22,780
he had an accident.

69
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:23,620
What?

70
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,060
How is he?

71
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:26,570
How is Junya?

72
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:27,920
Is he okay?

73
00:03:28,090 --> 00:03:28,890
He's in the hospital.

74
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,390
He got a fracture in his leg.

75
00:03:32,290 --> 00:03:33,720
But his life is not in danger.

76
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:35,320
Thank goodness.

77
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,660
What do we do

78
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:39,850
about the event?

79
00:03:40,710 --> 00:03:41,860
The press will arrive soon.

80
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:45,180
Let’s split up
and find a replacement.

81
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:46,690
Yes, sir.

82
00:03:46,980 --> 00:03:47,840
I'll let our head know.

83
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:48,890
Yes, sir.

84
00:04:39,290 --> 00:04:45,850


85
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:47,000
Yes.

86
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,860
That's right,
our model got into an accident.

87
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,330
Yes, right now.

88
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:52,550
This is urgent.

89
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:54,300
Is there anyone
who can model for us?

90
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,290
I'm Okita from TKG company.

91
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:58,840
Yes, we have an event today.

92
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:01,770
How did it go?

93
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,460
No luck.

94
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:07,650
Any update?

95
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,020
No one has found a substitute yet.

96
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,630
I see.

97
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:14,480
There's no choice.

98
00:05:15,890 --> 00:05:17,260
Does that mean we cancel the event?

99
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:22,330
I explained the situation
to Inspire’s Mr. Oishi.

100
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:25,980
But if Mr. Sakamoto can't come...

101
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:28,620
So we’re canceling?

102
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,590
He wants Takagi to do it.

103
00:05:33,860 --> 00:05:34,560
What?

104
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,130
Mr. Takagi instead of Junya?

105
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,150
No, that's...

106
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:38,890
I told them

107
00:05:39,890 --> 00:05:43,070
that might be a bit much as well.

108
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:45,440
But Mr. Oishi

109
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:48,610
seemed to really like you Mr. Takagi.

110
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:49,750
No, but...

111
00:05:49,970 --> 00:05:50,720
That's a good idea.

112
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,150
Yeah, I agree.

113
00:05:52,450 --> 00:05:53,940
This is better than canceling.

114
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:54,690
I agree.

115
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:57,370
We did our best to prepare
and set up everything for today.

116
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,750
As long as our client agrees,

117
00:05:58,960 --> 00:05:59,700
let's go with that.

118
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,470
What did Mr. Junya's agency say?

119
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:04,610
"We apologize for the inconvenience.
We'll leave the rest to you."

120
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:07,960
What?

121
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,300
Really?

122
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:11,080
He will be on stage?

123
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:13,340
People might recognize him as Toma.

124
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:14,990
No, I...

125
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,650


126
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,260
Excuse me.

127
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:25,830
Are you alright?

128
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,380
Yeah.

129
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,700
I'm sorry

130
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:30,240
that it’s come to this.

131
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:31,880
It's okay.

132
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,070
I’m just glad
your life isn’t in danger.

133
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:36,130
I heard about the situation.

134
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,560
We’re thinking of canceli...

135
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:39,460
Will you

136
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,060
stand on the stage on my behalf?

137
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,840
If it were anyone else,
I wouldn’t say this.

138
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:48,640
But

139
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:51,350
if it's you,
I know I can trust you with it.

140
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:57,750
Let’s just say I’m doing you a favor.

141
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,510
Don't push it.

142
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,060
Please.

143
00:07:06,330 --> 00:07:07,400
You’re all I can rely on.

144
00:07:15,890 --> 00:07:18,720
Thank you so much, everyone,
for coming by today.

145
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,380
Please allow me to start this event.

146
00:07:51,490 --> 00:07:53,240
He really is amazing.

147
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:55,990
He’s practically glowing.

148
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:57,550
He's so cool.

149
00:07:58,790 --> 00:07:59,550
Of course he is.

150
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,420
It feels right.

151
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,320
This is where Shuichi truly belongs.

152
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:24,530
Thank you very much for coming today.

153
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,260
Great job, everyone.

154
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:39,940
It was a job well done.

155
00:08:39,970 --> 00:08:41,460
Thank you so much.

156
00:08:43,730 --> 00:08:45,180
You looked so amazing back there.

157
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:46,630
Sir, you were so cool.

158
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,380
Thank you.

159
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:49,850
They asked a lot of questions too.
It ended so well.

160
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:54,000
Mr. Oishi, thank you for coming by.

161
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,150
It was splendid.

162
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,430
Job well done, everyone.

163
00:08:57,210 --> 00:08:57,910
Mr. Takagi.

164
00:08:57,990 --> 00:09:00,200
We owe the success
of this event to you.

165
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:01,370
Thank you.

166
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,560
It's my pleasure.

167
00:09:02,730 --> 00:09:05,550
You just became my idol.

168
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:06,890
Would you

169
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:08,920
consider becoming
our exclusive model?

170
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:11,930
What?

171
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:13,670
I'll think about it.

172
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:15,860
Thank you so much.

173
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:20,370
Excuse me.

174
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,300
Job well done.

175
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:25,470
Sir...

176
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:28,280
I mean, Shuichi,

177
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,510
you were so cool.

178
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:31,800
Thank you.

179
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,380
I got so nervous
since it's been a long time.

180
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,530
You looked so perfect...

181
00:09:41,860 --> 00:09:43,280
This is where I feel most at ease.

182
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:57,940
That mischievous smile.

183
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,370
I'm gonna remember it forever.

184
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:15,720
Excuse me.

185
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,930
You’re with TKG Company, right?

186
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:20,660
Yes.

187
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,550
I'm Harada
from Monthly Flow Magazine.

188
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,870
May I speak with you for a moment?

189
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,160
Sure.

190
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,610
But why me?

191
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,740
Everyone seems
to be so busy right now.

192
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:33,070
It’ll only take a minute,
if that's okay with you.

193
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:35,460
Okay.

194
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,480
Uhm.

195
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:45,840
Earlier,

196
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:48,490
you and Toma were talking so closely,
weren't you?

197
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,540
Oh.

198
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:51,840
Well...

199
00:10:54,730 --> 00:10:55,430
Wait.

200
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:56,660
Toma?

201
00:10:57,970 --> 00:10:58,780
What is

202
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,250
your relationship with Toma?

203
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,540
What are you

204
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:09,380
to Toma?

205
00:11:16,660 --> 00:11:18,190
That was my first ever experience.

206
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:23,750
Excuse me,
have you guys seen Ms. Nakajo?

207
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:24,600
What?

208
00:11:25,540 --> 00:11:26,310
Right.

209
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,350
I haven't seen her.

210
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:34,470
Toma?

211
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:36,830
Who is that?

212
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:38,540
Toma Kiryu.

213
00:11:38,950 --> 00:11:39,740
I know you know him.

214
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,210
Why were you two so close?

215
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:43,870
Ah well,

216
00:11:44,290 --> 00:11:46,310
I don't know what you mean.

217
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:47,720
Are you two dating?

218
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:49,460
Listen.

219
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,710
Break up with Toma.

220
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:53,970
I won’t let anyone
take Toma for themselves.

221
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,120
Break up with him now.

222
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:56,520
No.

223
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,320
Stay away from Toma.

224
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:03,810
Even now,

225
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,090
Toma is still my most favorite.

226
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:09,760
However...

227
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:13,900
However,

228
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,220
the one I fell in love with
is Shuichi Takagi.

229
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:18,860
What are you talking about?

230
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:20,880
Toma is Shuichi Takagi.

231
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,580
You're right.

232
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,420
But not totally.

233
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:25,210
What?

234
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:27,030
Hitomi?

235
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:28,870
What are you doing?

236
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:31,990
Toma.

237
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:33,750
Everyone is waiting for you.

238
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:35,740
Me too.

239
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,690
I've been waiting for you to come back.

240
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:39,860
I'm no longer Toma.

241
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:42,670
What are you saying?
You are Toma.

242
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:44,850
I am Shuichi Takagi.

243
00:12:49,890 --> 00:12:50,590
To be honest,

244
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:52,770
I didn't know
the purpose of my existence.

245
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,370
Then I discovered myself
who likes acting.

246
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:00,130
I thought acting
was the path of my life.

247
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:01,880
That's right.

248
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:04,990
That's why you should stay
as Toma forever.

249
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:08,240
No, that's wrong.

250
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:11,380
I am

251
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:13,870
no longer the actor Toma Kiryu.

252
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:16,860
I am Shuichi Takagi

253
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:18,930
of TKG company.

254
00:13:27,230 --> 00:13:27,930
At first,

255
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:32,030
I was unsure
if I could do well in the company.

256
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:34,410
But...

257
00:13:34,830 --> 00:13:35,630
That's okay.

258
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:36,460
Keep on acting.

259
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:37,860
What?

260
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:39,040
Someday,

261
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,090
your acting might turn
into a reality.

262
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,070
Our manager is compassionate.

263
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:44,800
He is very responsible.

264
00:13:45,420 --> 00:13:46,270
How can you say so?

265
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,380
He just joined us recently.

266
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:49,480
But I can tell.

267
00:13:51,850 --> 00:13:53,910
Everyone welcomed me warmly.

268
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,280
I wanted to keep working

269
00:13:57,130 --> 00:13:58,550
with my team at this company.

270
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:01,550
Go.

271
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:06,300
I finally found a place
to live as Shuichi Takagi.

272
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,800
That's why

273
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:13,910
I'll keep on living the way I am now.

274
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:16,830
Please understand.

275
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:21,380
So?

276
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:22,950
What am I gonna do now?

277
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:25,180
Then what was I doing with my life?

278
00:14:26,020 --> 00:14:28,050
Toma exists forever in my heart.

279
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:29,340
He will never disappear.

280
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,700
That goes

281
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:33,900
the same with me.

282
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:39,130
Even if Toma chose a new path,

283
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,940
and start living as Shuichi.

284
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:47,640
Even so, Toma will never disappear
from our hearts.

285
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,100
For fans like us,

286
00:14:53,390 --> 00:14:55,130
Toma's existence had a great impact.

287
00:15:02,370 --> 00:15:03,070
He was

288
